# Python via uv

All Python work in this project is done through [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/). Do not use `pip`, `pip install`, `poetry`, `conda`, or bare `python`/`python3` for project tasks.

## Package management

- Dependencies live in `pyproject.toml`; lockfile is `uv.lock`.
- Install/sync: `uv sync`
- Add/remove: `uv add <pkg>`, `uv remove <pkg>`
- Dev deps: `uv add --dev <pkg>`

## Running code

- Scripts and modules: `uv run python script.py`, `uv run -m module`
- CLI tools from deps: `uv run pytest`, `uv run ruff check`, etc.
- One-off tools without adding to project: `uv tool run <tool>`

## Environments

- Prefer the project venv managed by uv (`.venv` after `uv sync`).
- Create/sync explicitly when needed: `uv venv`, then `uv sync`
- Do not manually `source` another venv or install packages outside uv.

## New Python setup

When bootstrapping Python in this repo:

```bash
uv init          # if no pyproject.toml yet
uv add <deps>
uv sync
```

## Do not

- `pip install ...` (use `uv add` or `uv pip install` only inside uv-managed contexts if truly needed)
- `python -m venv` / `virtualenv` for this project
- `poetry add`, `conda install`, or global interpreter installs for project deps
